Hey there, as of now I'm keeping ATC24 closed source for following reasons:
The development at this early stage is still very complex with lots of self-written utility classes and libraries, with the principle of "I will self-test as much as I can, and push hotfixes to errors users encounter afterwards".
I honestly admit that I do not like the idea of the "Roblox Community" having my code freely available to copy and use themselves at all. While you can of course simply download the website via sketchy tools, going open source would just be giving some people the carte blanche to do whatever.
While the idea of having the community involved in development of this software is indeed a very appealing thought, these are my main 2 reasons. Maybe I will consider going open source when I personally drop support for this app, but thats a very far future.

Bugfixes and Errors 2!


Changes
* Added a message for server restarts
* Added more precise error messages to aid the user in resolving common issues
* Connection to server is not closed by errors anymore

Hotfixes
* Fixed an issue where leaving rooms was broken

Internal Changes

* In accordance with logs of the past few hours of operation, added MORE failsafes to the server in case clients send faulty data.

Happy Controlling!
- Zedruc
